<div class="row">
 <div align="center" class="col-xs-12"><h2><b>7. Divisional Charts</b></h2></div><!--/.col-xs-12 -->
</div><!--/.row -->
<div class="row">
 <div class="col-xs-12">
   <div>Sage Parasara defined 16 different divisions of rasis. Jaimini and Tajaka writers mentioned 4 more divisions.</div>
   <div class="table-responsive">
	<table class="table">
	 <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>S.No.</th>
        <th>Divisional Chart</th>
        <th>Symbol</th>
        <th>Area of life to be seen from it</th>
      </tr>
     </thead>
     <tbody>
      <tr><td>1</td><td>Rasi</td><td>D-1</td><td>Existence at the physical level</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>2</td><td>Hora</td><td>D-2</td><td>Wealth and money</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>3</td><td>Drekkana</td><td>D-3</td><td>Everything related to brothers and sisters</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>4</td><td>Chaturthamsa</td><td>D-4</td><td>Residence, houses owned, properties and fortune</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>5</td><td>Panchamsa</td><td>D-5</td><td>Fame, authority and power</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>6</td><td>Shashthamsa</td><td>D-6</td><td>Health troubles</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>7</td><td>Saptamsa</td><td>D-7</td><td>Everything related to children (and grand-children)</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>8</td><td>Ashtamsa</td><td>D-8</td><td>Sudden and unexpected troubles, litigation etc</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>9</td><td>Navamsa</td><td>D-9</td><td>Marriage and everything related to spouse(s),dharma (duty and righteousness), <br/>
											 interaction with other people, basic skills, inner self</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>10</td><td>Dasamsa</td><td>D-10</td><td>Career, activities and achievements in society</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>11</td><td>Rudramsa</td><td>D-11</td><td>Death and destruction</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>12</td><td>Dwadasamsa</td><td>D-12</td><td>Everything related to parents (also uncles, aunts
											   and grand-parents,<br/> i.e. blood-relatives of parents)</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>13</td><td>Shodasamsa</td><td>D-16</td><td>Vehicles, pleasures, comforts and discomforts</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>14</td><td>Vimsamsa</td><td>D-20</td><td>Religious activities and spiritual matters</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>15</td><td>Chaturvimsamsa</td><td>D-24</td><td>Learning, knowledge and education</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>16</td><td>Nakshatramsa</td><td>D-27</td><td>Strengths and weaknesses, inherent nature</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>17</td><td>Trimsamsa</td><td>D-30</td><td>Evils and punishment, sub-conscious self, some
														diseases</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>18</td><td>Khavedamsa</td><td>D-40</td><td>Auspicious and inauspicious events</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>19</td><td>Akshavedamsa</td><td>D-45</td><td>All matters</td></tr>
	  <tr><td>20</td><td>Shashtyamsa</td><td>D-60</td><td>Karma of past life, all matters</td></tr>
     </tbody>
	</table>
   </div><!--/.table-responsive -->
 </div><!--/.col-xs-12 -->
</div><!--/.row -->